title.narrative: Enterprise Development for Global Competitiveness Project

description.narrative: (West Bank and Gaza): The Compete Project aims to strengthen the Palestinian private sector, foster sustainable economic growth, prosperity, and regional stability. In FY 2014, USAID will use $14.9 million of FY 2014 ESF funds to assist Palestinian firms to compete in global markets through innovation, skills-trainings, and linking enterprises to valuable supply chains. USAID will also assist in the development of Palestinian service providers and business support organizations in order to create a market-friendly sustainable business environment. The project will focus on four high-priority sectors including agribusiness, tourism, stone & marble, and information communications technology (ICT).Within both the agribusiness and the stone & marble sectors, USAID will enable Palestinian producers to reach new markets previously thought inaccessible to West Bank firms, increasing private sector investment and facilitating new Palestinian exports. The project will assist Palestinian firms to produce high-value products and services at internationally recognized standards for quality and production. USAID will also support Palestinian enterprises to integrate new modern technologies and techniques to reduce production costs; increase access to inputs such as quality water, land, labor and, boost environmental sustainability. Within the ICT sector, USAID will facilitate private sector partnerships between US multinationals and Palestinian firms to boost exports, improve skills, and develop new market channels. The project will also support Palestinian tech firms and entrepreneurs through training and develop service providers to support a greater pipeline of highly skilled labor and accelerate promising technology start-ups.Within tourism, USAID will assist the sector to strategically position Bethlehem, Jericho, and Nablus as first-rate tourist destinations with their respective religious, historic, and cultural significance.
